# Sprint contract: MVP-02-admin-ui-status-view-001

Status: `BUILT_AWAITING_VERIFIER`
Created: 2026-05-11
Stage: `mvp`
Parent stage unit: `MVP-02.04`
Execution mode: minimal admin UI/scaffold implementation slice after this freeze

## Objective

Implement the smallest screenshotable `apps/admin` operator status view for the already verified backend code-status DTO.

This contract exists because `MVP-02-admin-code-status-view-001` proved only the backend/admin API. `MVP-02.04` still needs an admin UI/status view with browser and screenshot evidence. The builder must keep this as one narrow `apps/admin` scaffold plus read-only view, not a full admin/CMS product.

## Current verified baseline to preserve

- `.agent/stages/mvp/status.json` state is `VERIFIED_BACKEND_API_PASS_UI_OPEN`.
- Latest verified sprint is `MVP-02-admin-code-status-view-001`.
- `MVP-02.01`, `MVP-02.02`, `MVP-02.03` are `PASS`.
- Backend/API-only part of `MVP-02.04` is `PASS`.
- `apps/admin` UI/status view is not implemented.
- Full `MVP-02.04`, full `MVP-02` and MVP stage are not complete.
- Human gates remain open: legal/privacy, real employee/customer data, customer-specific reporting, admin auth/role/audit policy.

## Backend DTO source

Use the proven backend contract as the DTO baseline:

- `GET /api/v1/admin/tenants/{tenantId}/cohorts/{cohortId}/code-status`;
- optional `status`, `page`, `size`;
- status enum: `CREATED | ISSUED | RESERVED | ACTIVATED | REVOKED | EXPIRED`;
- size max: `100`;
- response records:
  - `tenantId`, `cohortId`, `cohortKey`, `cohortName`, `cohortKind`, `cohortStatus`, `targetSize`;
  - `summary.issuedCount`, `activatedCount`, `registeredCount`, `revokedCount`, `expiredCount`, `totalCodeCount`, `remainingCapacity`;
  - `statusCounts[]` with `{ status, count }`;
  - `codes.page`, `codes.size`, `codes.totalItems`, `codes.totalPages`;
  - `codes.items[]` with `inviteCodeId`, `status`, `issuedAt`, `expiresAt`, `activatedAt`, `registeredAt`, `registered`.

The UI must not render raw invite code values, lookup hashes, activation subject refs, employee fullName/email/phone, diagnostics, weak zones or financial data.

## Files in scope for future builder

Production files allowed only within this contract:

- `apps/admin/package.json`;
- `apps/admin/next.config.mjs`;
- `apps/admin/tsconfig.json`;
- `apps/admin/app/layout.tsx`;
- `apps/admin/app/page.tsx`;
- `apps/admin/app/globals.css`;
- narrow `apps/admin/app/loading.tsx`, `apps/admin/app/error.tsx`, `apps/admin/components/**`, `apps/admin/lib/**` and `apps/admin/tests/**` files if needed for UI states, DTO typing, fixture/live fetch boundary and focused tests;
- root `package.json`, `pnpm-lock.yaml` and `Makefile` only if required to install/build/typecheck the admin app and wire `make verify`, `make test-unit`, `make build` honestly;
- `README.md`, `docs/setup/codex-setup.md`, `docs/architecture/repo-layout.md` or `docs/architecture/source-of-truth.md` only if setup/runtime/workflow documentation must be synchronized after root wrapper or app baseline changes;
- `packages/api-client/**` is out of scope unless generated from an existing generator. Because no generator/artifacts currently exist, expected action is an explicit generated-client no-op note.

Stage artifacts:

- `.agent/stages/mvp/evidence.*`;
- `.agent/stages/mvp/evidence/MVP-02-admin-ui-status-view-001.*`;
- `.agent/stages/mvp/raw/**`;
- `.agent/stages/mvp/verdict.*`;
- `.agent/stages/mvp/verdicts/MVP-02-admin-ui-status-view-001.json`;
- `.agent/stages/mvp/problems.*`;
- `.agent/stages/mvp/problems/MVP-02-admin-ui-status-view-001.md`;
- current stage handoff artifacts as needed.

## Out of scope

- Backend/API/schema changes, except optional read-only smoke against the existing endpoint.
- New OpenAPI contract or generated API client implementation.
- Manual generated artifacts in `packages/api-client`.
- Admin auth/session/roles/audit production policy.
- Real employee/customer data, customer-specific reporting and HR dashboard.
- Admin mutations: generate, revoke, create tenant/cohort, bulk edit, export or status mutation.
- Employee-facing web UI, onboarding, privacy/consent/legal screens.
- Diagnostics, learning, content/CMS, rewards, merch, support, feedback or pilot outcome reporting.
- Full `MVP-02.04`, full `MVP-02` or MVP closure before fresh verification.

## Acceptance criteria

1. Backend baseline remains Spring Boot, Java 21, Maven Wrapper, PostgreSQL, Flyway and OpenAPI/springdoc; this slice does not change backend behavior.
2. `apps/admin` has a minimal Next.js + React scaffold with package scripts sufficient for install, typecheck, build and focused test/smoke checks.
3. The default admin route renders a read-only cohort/code status view from a typed local DTO boundary matching the proven backend response.
4. The view includes Russian operator copy and clear success, loading, error and empty states.
5. Success state shows cohort metadata, summary/funnel counts, status counts, filter/page state and paginated code rows.
6. UI status filters use only `CREATED`, `ISSUED`, `RESERVED`, `ACTIVATED`, `REVOKED`, `EXPIRED`; page size is bounded at `100`.
7. A synthetic fixture mode is available for screenshots and tests without real customer/employee data.
8. Optional live mode, if implemented, is read-only and calls only the existing backend endpoint using configured synthetic tenant/cohort IDs.
9. UI source, fixtures, rendered output and screenshots do not include raw invite codes, lookup hashes, activation subject refs, employee `fullName`, `email`, `phone`, diagnostics, weak zones, exact financial data, real customer brand or real data.
10. Root `make verify`, `make test-unit` and `make build` include relevant admin checks after the admin app exists, or evidence records exact honest substitutes if a wrapper cannot include a command yet.
11. Relevant admin package commands are run and recorded.
12. Browser smoke and screenshots cover desktop and mobile admin route.
13. Generated-client status is an explicit no-op because `packages/api-client` has no generator/artifacts, unless the builder stops and re-freezes generated-client scope.
14. Documentation sync is handled: update narrow setup/runtime docs if root wrapper or app setup changed; otherwise record no canonical docs change needed.
15. Evidence maps every criterion to raw refs for commands, package checks, browser smoke/screenshots, DTO/fixture check, PII/raw-code scan, generated-client no-op, docs target decision, harness validation and fresh verifier verdict.
16. Human gates remain open and are not marked `DONE`.

## Verification evidence required later

Record raw outputs for:

- `git status --short`;
- `java -version`;
- `cd apps/api && ./mvnw -v`;
- `make verify`;
- `make test-unit`;
- `make build`;
- `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` or equivalent install proof after lockfile changes;
- admin package typecheck/build/test commands, for example:
  - `pnpm --filter <admin-package-name> typecheck`;
  - `pnpm --filter <admin-package-name> build`;
  - `pnpm --filter <admin-package-name> test` when defined;
- browser smoke for the admin route;
- desktop and mobile screenshot refs;
- DTO/fixture/client boundary validation;
- optional live read-only endpoint smoke, only with synthetic local data;
- PII/raw-code/customer-brand scan;
- generated-client no-op note;
- docs target decision and any canonical docs updated;
- `python3 .agents/skills/stage-launch-proof-loop/scripts/verify_harness.py --stage-id mvp`;
- fresh `stage_verifier` verdict scoped only to `MVP-02-admin-ui-status-view-001`.

## Docs targets

- Primary proof target: `.agent/stages/mvp/evidence/MVP-02-admin-ui-status-view-001.*`.
- If root commands, package scripts or app setup change developer workflow, update the narrowest canonical setup/runtime doc:
  - `README.md`;
  - `docs/setup/codex-setup.md`;
  - `docs/architecture/repo-layout.md`;
  - `docs/architecture/source-of-truth.md` only for architecture baseline drift.
- No canonical product/stage doc change is expected unless builder discovers a contradiction.
- Generated-client notes must be recorded as no-op unless a generator exists.

## Diagram expectations

Evidence must include a Mermaid flow or sequence diagram for:

`Admin browser route -> local typed status client/fixture boundary -> existing backend code-status endpoint or synthetic DTO -> privacy-safe status cards/table -> loading/error/empty/success states`.

If both fixture and live modes exist, the diagram must show how mode selection works and where synthetic-only data is enforced.

## Human gates

No human gate is closed by this contract.

The following remain `WAITING_HUMAN`:

- legal/privacy wording;
- consent copy;
- real employee/customer data processing;
- customer-specific reporting boundaries;
- admin auth/role/audit policy for production use;
- any disclosure of personal employee contact fields, financial answers, diagnostic weak zones or below-threshold reporting.

## Current state

Builder implementation and evidence are recorded for this UI slice:

- immutable evidence: `.agent/stages/mvp/evidence/MVP-02-admin-ui-status-view-001.md`;
- raw command refs: `.agent/stages/mvp/raw/orchestrator-mvp-02-admin-ui-status-view-001-*`;
- screenshot refs: `.agent/stages/mvp/raw/mvp-02-admin-ui-status-view-001-screenshots-final/*`;
- implementation is under `apps/admin` with root wrapper/doc updates;
- backend/API/schema and generated client implementation remain untouched/out of scope.

Fresh `stage_verifier` is still required. Do not mark `MVP-02-admin-ui-status-view-001`, full `MVP-02.04`, full `MVP-02` or MVP complete until fresh verification passes.

