docs/architecture/repo-layout.md:52:### `apps/admin`
docs/architecture/repo-layout.md:56:Current MVP-02 admin baseline: a minimal Next.js app renders a read-only cohort/code status view from the verified backend DTO. It uses synthetic fixture mode by default; generated API client integration remains a no-op until `packages/api-client` has a generator/artifacts.
docs/architecture/repo-layout.md:89:`apps/api` now contains a minimal Spring Boot + Maven Wrapper backend baseline. The first append-only domain migration after `V001` introduces tenant, cohort/wave and invite-code tables for the corporate pilot access model. There is no public API/controller surface in this slice; frontend/admin contract generation remains unchanged until an explicit API slice.
docs/architecture/repo-layout.md:91:## MVP-02 admin UI baseline
docs/architecture/repo-layout.md:93:`apps/admin` now contains a minimal Next.js + React scaffold for the read-only cohort/code status view. Root `make verify`, `make test-unit` and `make build` include the available admin checks. The admin UI must keep using privacy-safe DTO fields only and must not expose raw invite codes or employee contact data.
docs/setup/codex-setup.md:78:make verify
docs/setup/codex-setup.md:79:make test-unit
docs/setup/codex-setup.md:81:make build
docs/setup/codex-setup.md:84:После первого MVP-02 backend slice `make verify` and `make test-unit` also run backend unit checks through `apps/api/mvnw`. После минимального `apps/admin` UI slice `make verify` runs admin typecheck/test, `make test-unit` runs focused admin tests, and `make build` builds the admin app before packaging `apps/api` with tests skipped after the explicit verification steps.
